    <Folder>
      <name>Fishing locations</name>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Ana Reservoir</name>
        <description><![CDATA[This is a 60-acrereservoir located about 23 miles northeast of Paisley, Oregon. This reservoirmaintains a temperature of about 58 degrees and is open year around. It isstocked with hybrid bass and rainbow trout. Boats can be launched from animproved ramp and an accessible dock is available. Many anglers target hybridbass January to March using crankbaits (e.g. Rapala’s) from the shore, butthese fish can be caught anytime during the year. Anglers using boats can trollcrankbaits or jig for hybrid bass. Check the regulations for special conditionsthat exist for harvesting hybrid bass. Trout fishing can be good anytime of theyear because water temperatures keep them active. Bait, lures, flies, ortrolling will be productive for trout.<br> <br>Fish species: hybrid (white/striped) bass, rainbow trout, chub<br> <br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southeast-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1573-0F9D58</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -120.749488,42.997632,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Ana River</name>
        <description><![CDATA[This is a spring-fed river that begins at the Ana Reservoir dam and continues through Summer Lake Wildlife Area (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/visitors/summer_lake_wildlife_area.asp). Sampling has identified substantially higher numbers of trout in the first 5.5 miles or the river. The water temperature remains about 58 degrees and is optimal for rainbow trout. Bait can be used on this river. Bait, lures, and flies are all effective methods for catching rainbow trout. <br> <br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout, chub<br> <br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southeast-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1573-0F9D58</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -120.744596,42.992814,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Antelope Flat Reservoir</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5zKpcKnkhcQytxAzJm_qzFyK2bd62tleY-flXKYY3RO3bRQjKAnhv88x3MHE2GcfJhRSm3zyXBkkY61JssH8ABHXzUCwNKYM4iHZBMRGrOtbQ5SmNJ17kUGOQdO4p4C2CXgYjrYRPycNQUUyMk90Cv1HKAiEBB2cZ8jlc" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is a 170-acre reservoir located in the Maury Mountain area of the Ochoco National Forest (http://www.fs.usda.gov/wps/portal/fsinternet/!ut/p/c4/04_SB8K8xLLM9MSSzPy8xBz9CP0os3gjAwhwtDDw9_AI8zPyhQoY6BdkOyoCAGixyPg!/?ss=110601&navtype=BROWSEBYSUBJECT&cid=fsbdev3_036040&navid=091000000000000&pnavid=null&position=Welcome.Html&ttype=detail&pname=Deschutes%20&%20Ochoco%20National%20Forests%20&%20Crooked%20River%20National%20Grassland-%20Home), 30 miles southeast of Prineville. Antelope Flat Reservoir Campground (http://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/centraloregon/recarea/?recid=38784) and boat ramp are located at the west end of the reservoir. This a very productive reservoir with excellent opportunities for rainbow trout 14-18 inches. Flies, lures and bait are all effective. Bank angling opportunities are present, however, anglers in boats or float tubes tend to be more successful.<br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout<br> <br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southeast-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5zKpcKnkhcQytxAzJm_qzFyK2bd62tleY-flXKYY3RO3bRQjKAnhv88x3MHE2GcfJhRSm3zyXBkkY61JssH8ABHXzUCwNKYM4iHZBMRGrOtbQ5SmNJ17kUGOQdO4p4C2CXgYjrYRPycNQUUyMk90Cv1HKAiEBB2cZ8jlc</value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -120.377197,44.040219,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Badger Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[This is a small lake located on the southeast slope of Mt. Hood, within the Mt. Hood National Forest (http://www.fs.usda.gov/mthood). Access to this lake is via a steep, primitive forest road that is usually closed during the winter months.<br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/RR/central/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/reg_changes/index.asp)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -121.559161,45.303071,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Baker Pond</name>
        <description><![CDATA[This is a 2-acre pond located in the White River Wildlife Area (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/visitors/white_river_wildlife_area.asp) in Wasco County about 10 miles south of Dufur, Oregon. This spring-fed lake is stocked in the spring and generally open from April through October.<br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout, brown bullhead<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/central-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -121.323561,45.343202,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Beulah Reservoir</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v6PcuAkMHVkUrLqVnyUKCg6HZjj-l-hgdlaobUR_Kh_ZT_19wrdHQ4PD_54qDr2eCn_emB33GOCGs2poVgJszL6-gDm02InDVHUudJDHNE8AqYFcacNfrT6kJt5ubsXgDwhrJWTOn5Oxr53ucK4j1p8SNe0s_c" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is a 2,060-acre irrigation reservoir located on the North Fork Malheur River 19 miles north of Juntura, Oregon. It is open year round to trout fishing. The reservoir supports populations of bull trout, redband trout, and whitefish. The resevoir is stocked in the spring when enough water is present to support trout into the fall. Camping sites exist at the boat ramp and along the eastern shore. Best fishing occurs in the spring from ice out until June. Fishing improves again in the fall after water temperatures cool<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout<br> <br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southeast-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v6PcuAkMHVkUrLqVnyUKCg6HZjj-l-hgdlaobUR_Kh_ZT_19wrdHQ4PD_54qDr2eCn_emB33GOCGs2poVgJszL6-gDm02InDVHUudJDHNE8AqYFcacNfrT6kJt5ubsXgDwhrJWTOn5Oxr53ucK4j1p8SNe0s_c</value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -118.114014,43.905808,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Big Cultus Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v66TB1pmoT8dFGNo9tpbkP5-d8FyLMZAqe10JJXEUQ0jdmzzDe2k3Uhy9jBZwjZmFJKP8Vvbz2NAu2gQNZPoGwh7xMojFHMREC9z_FWq3b9mj3E2QEK6ahUDG5dJkCAKtFJEJ6sYwasznx2d7UvS5IVX_jZFw" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is a 785-acre lake located about 50 miles south of Bend, Oregon in the Deschutes National Forest (http://www.fs.usda.gov/centraloregon). This lake is deep and holds lake trout in addition to stocked rainbows. There is a resort (http://www.cultuslakeresort.com/) on the southeast shore of the lake, with restaurant, boat and motor rentals, cabins, supplies and gas. Cultus Lake Campground (http://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/centraloregon/recreation/camping-cabins/recarea/?recid=38836&actid=29) is a large campground with sites for RVs up to 30 feet. For campers who want more privacy West Cultus Campground (http://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/centraloregon/recreation/camping-cabins/recarea/?recid=39028&actid=29) offers boat-in only campsites. In addition to fishing, activities at Big Cultus Lake include swimming, water skiing and hiking.<br> <br>Fish species: lake trout, stocked rainbow trout, brook trout<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/central-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v66TB1pmoT8dFGNo9tpbkP5-d8FyLMZAqe10JJXEUQ0jdmzzDe2k3Uhy9jBZwjZmFJKP8Vvbz2NAu2gQNZPoGwh7xMojFHMREC9z_FWq3b9mj3E2QEK6ahUDG5dJkCAKtFJEJ6sYwasznx2d7UvS5IVX_jZFw</value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -121.837993,43.82883,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Big Lava Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v56JWqF7plSvNbF99Hzc_4-H37Igb0YwYzN8IZBTWrOFxLAgjDn1yOmFnqXnxNo-5M8GfMWou-f5V0bnxv9ZmQid0CGokRsTz5onuILfGg90zBLaSdAmMhFgYdsC5f_C1nBjWaJzV-Dc1PPMMrMfdIkDQ" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is a 160-acre lake located within the Deschutes National Forest (http://www.fs.usda.gov/centraloregon) approximately 38 miles south of Bend, Oregon. This beautiful spring-fed lake reaches a maximum depth of about 30 feet and supports populations of brook trout and rainbow trout. Camping and a boat ramp are available at Lava Lake Campground (http://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/centraloregon/recreation/camping-cabins/recarea/?recid=38894&actid=29) on the south shore. There is also a private resort with RV hook-ups, boat rentals and supplies. Boats are subject to a 10 m.p.h. speed limit.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, brook trout.<br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/central-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v56JWqF7plSvNbF99Hzc_4-H37Igb0YwYzN8IZBTWrOFxLAgjDn1yOmFnqXnxNo-5M8GfMWou-f5V0bnxv9ZmQid0CGokRsTz5onuILfGg90zBLaSdAmMhFgYdsC5f_C1nBjWaJzV-Dc1PPMMrMfdIkDQ</value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -121.767783,43.914589,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Big Rock Reservoir</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5kEl6mqEQi25QuiVGgAN1U1bXfytmk3s27n1evjy8DTfSsSQFbtX0Cxb5RGefGziSItHVBEA9Ghk2awnYTno0UDlzjihz2IPutUq3OyFGYKcpc1vtYGpc-tgowRmQi-aegjzzFSgBcG5wY-0wSDiBz7fDVGChn0M7X" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is a 5-acre reservoir located 15 north of Plush, Oregon within the Bureau of Land Management's Lakeview, Oregon District (http://www.blm.gov/or/districts/lakeview/index.php). This reservoir is stocked with fingerling rainbow trout annually and has the capacity to grow fish up to 16”. The reservoir can summer kill (algae bloom) occasionally as happened in 2011. The reservoir was re-stocked in 2012. This is a great little reservoir to float tube and the fish are very willing to bite because they don’t get much fishing pressure. The reservoir does not show up on current BLM maps, but is located in Mary Ann Draw. Use BLM Road #6105 to access Mary Ann Draw.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout<br> <br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southeast-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1573-0F9D58</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
