      <Placemark>
        <name>Bikini Pond</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5nll5C34C4He0QlLHIlK_csMTGVgCiBngdV4RR9r_40v2XTyJ0S5U1yhbVy4LBmP9_saL3WLbEJ_7kyhFihM-JEfkzXdql4-tdsCXyQr4WWrLtNJECqk7vQF3-W9HwXf1Td5fpHEsrLcCdS76eyBtK" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is a 4-acre pond next to the Columbia River in Mayer State Park (http://www.oregonstateparks.org/park_161.php) between Hood River and The Dalles, Oregon. There is a picnic area, accessible restrooms, and paved parking area. Fishing is from the bank, although the park also provides access to the Columbia River.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, warmwater species<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/central-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
