            -121.290168,45.683364,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Blue Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v4ylhnx4pU4u3qxJaB1JCLcjdORN4WaeMYXXohNXI3Pv_Gz04eTCYLv1nXofmvKhqaFhqXG00a0GTEbQIrtlUNAUbHLn4PYBlZS3UbUZqJ0aO7fjDL7nCZjugq9vysLewmiPsW8AimskmELXbXDDUfhtg" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is a 20-acre lake located in the Fremont-Winema National Forest (http://www.fs.usda.gov/fremont-winema) in the Gearheart Mountain Wilderness (http://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/fremont-winema/recreation/camping-cabins/recarea/?recid=60171&actid=34). The lake is accessed via a 3-mile trail off of NF-3372. The trailhead is about equal distances from Bly, Paisley, or Lakeview. This lake makes a great day trip or overnight camping excursion. Fingerling rainbow trout are stocked annually with mules and help from the High Desert Trail Riders. Bait, flies, and lures all work well for trout from 6”-16”.<br> <br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout<br> <br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southeast-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1573-0F9D58</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v4ylhnx4pU4u3qxJaB1JCLcjdORN4WaeMYXXohNXI3Pv_Gz04eTCYLv1nXofmvKhqaFhqXG00a0GTEbQIrtlUNAUbHLn4PYBlZS3UbUZqJ0aO7fjDL7nCZjugq9vysLewmiPsW8AimskmELXbXDDUfhtg</value>
