        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Bully Creek Reservoir</name>
        <description><![CDATA[This is a 1,001-acre irrigation reservoir located about 9.5 miles west of Vale Oregon via Grand Blvd and Bully Creek Road. This reservoir is managed primarily for warmwater fish, but on dry years rainbow trout have been stocked into the reservoir when most other water bodies are dry.<br> <br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout<br> <br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southeast-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -117.402649,44.023187,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Burns Pond</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5KU2Kt64mChg25ZV2lgbYPkW6syKJKypjM0JT8NpDCfSg_o4ChCoPCfVUNw7nNCP6Vck2RtkhSsaN-LdXXHA3hOi2fke0GV4zIQkTSHFuRlKFQXmZtKN9iR6HOvZsObTi88-CvcLDmlANHeCO86Bs" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is a small pond located on the south side of Hwy. 78 approximately two miles east of Burns, Ore. The pond has good access and is sometimes used for family fishing events. Facilities include picnic tables and an accessible fishing dock.<br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southeast-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
