            -119.00864,43.585505,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Campbell Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5iuPVci6Y-q_tzwBK99h_Ejx94lvscsfmSqywa5rCe5ejJ8_ivuqBu2LioXw9B2-UxAuyv429w8eWYvuMo2fomNRtn2Jv5eRMSA3uEPmQy0i0P64WTcOykLMmdsAWV4O6zebh3oq6FJBP6nKakmwPft9M" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Thisis a 21-acre lake located in a high mountain setting on the Fremont-WinemaNational Forest (http://www.fs.usda.gov/fremont-winema) approximately 30 miles southeast of Paisley, Oregon.Located at an elevation of 7,195 ft., this lake is not accessible until late-Junebecause of snow. The lake is stocked annually with legal- and trophy-sizedrainbow trout. Small boats can be launched from a boat ramp at Campbell Lake Campground (http://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/fremont-winema/recreation/camping-cabins/recarea/?recid=59755&actid=29) but are restricted toelectric motors and a 5 m.p.h. speed limit. Camping is also available nearby atDead Horse Lake Campground (http://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/fremont-winema/recreation/camping-cabins/recarea/?recid=59761&actid=29).<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southeast-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1573-0F9D58</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5iuPVci6Y-q_tzwBK99h_Ejx94lvscsfmSqywa5rCe5ejJ8_ivuqBu2LioXw9B2-UxAuyv429w8eWYvuMo2fomNRtn2Jv5eRMSA3uEPmQy0i0P64WTcOykLMmdsAWV4O6zebh3oq6FJBP6nKakmwPft9M</value>
