            -120.754461,42.563646,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Chewaucan River</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v6QP97vPECl7A4SKSPde9Axadc9eLnVNILzQlUYw1uIa5BdqPzdla5lXjCeea_mV83t0uPhwNlfD6nH2Vl_NrLxNmccv57Y8t2p_oMrBt0WZa9Elx4MrZs-RLB8HCyDLKwspLjIGbOT_vvqDYtHN37QV1VYH7zchw" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>The river has mixed private-U.S. Forest Service ownership but has many public access points on the tributaries and mainstem river. The river is managed for native redband trout and has multiple campgrounds to stage from. Special harvest and gear regulations are in effect on the river. Native redband trout range from 10-20+ inches. The lower river (below Hwy 31) has largemouth bass near Rivers End Reservoir, a private reservoir. Most bass are 6”-10” long, and brown bullhead catfish are also present, but small.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, redband trout, bass, catfish<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southeast-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1573-0F9D58</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v6QP97vPECl7A4SKSPde9Axadc9eLnVNILzQlUYw1uIa5BdqPzdla5lXjCeea_mV83t0uPhwNlfD6nH2Vl_NrLxNmccv57Y8t2p_oMrBt0WZa9Elx4MrZs-RLB8HCyDLKwspLjIGbOT_vvqDYtHN37QV1VYH7zchw</value>
