      <Placemark>
        <name>Chickahominy Reservoir</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v476N6gETL1sxqFvNGEvSztnExTagxcTrLhuxZEydasSA0gcMgzf0Pec44ypom4PmFG2gS4cKXeriqEuGu3ug_CSB0XPnijwJZzlREUr6Q1uP4Maa6oR6bspV6HSCDWe_b0M90MSK3GQHGO5kof3lIUgnDkthMPgRy3Nw" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is a 530-acre reservoir in Oregon's high desert, located approximately 32 miles west of Burns. It is heavily stocked with fingerling trout in the spring and is known for producing some large rainbows. There is a boat ramp, and many anglers troll for trout while others fish from the shore. There is a boat ramp on the southeast end of the reservoir, accessed by a gravel road.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southeast-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
