      <Placemark>
        <name>Clear Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v7TsbxKO0_sZR4lBRU6iC9-wL_LTs9e7jVd7ou2ps8XJOrpfA5_yvlAdNPKCqBG7_edKFi-v79hhZo7hSQNOjlDTOEHGoQlEsi_ZNQjvHlzMx-KQoUmgPxrqFXSLlYkGBLCW9RHeZyzyXRUKDN3_E8" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is a beautiful lake located within the Mt. Hood National Forest (http://www.fs.usda.gov/mthood) on the east side of Mt. Hood, about 12 miles from Government Camp, Oregon. A boat ramp, picnic area and campsites are located at Clear Lake Campground (http://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/mthood/recreation/wateractivities/recarea/?recid=53058&actid=78) on the east side of the lake.<br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/central-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
