      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Cottonwood Meadows Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v49zTFri1WgJt_WpgII7gzr4srH4CK049l846HMAEsWKFuDEbLCCUx7Sim7n09BeggRrGO5gu2alcL-SjGNChywlFkXUPQKHk0b3DLvp7uJ2dN0xQNFhevi94Do2YcI25nRifsesuXHKl4IoCk6FRTxnrpj" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Thisis a 42-acre lake located on the Fremont-Winema National Forest (http://www.fs.usda.gov/fremont-winema) about 22 miles northwest ofLakeview, Oregon. It is located at an elevation of 6,130 feet and subject to heavy snowfall. The lake is open year-round but access may at times be limited to snowmobile, snow shoes or dog sleds. This lake is stockedannually with rainbow and brook trout persist through natural production. Thereare two campgrounds on the lake, and two cement boat ramps, although motors arerestricted to electric only.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, brook trout<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southeast-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)<br><br><img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5QCVKKTliCBO44kWXxiJKJcXnylU6tU-wx2y5py3c8E22AWyega9JOySQ" height="200" width="auto" />]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1573-0F9D58</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v49zTFri1WgJt_WpgII7gzr4srH4CK049l846HMAEsWKFuDEbLCCUx7Sim7n09BeggRrGO5gu2alcL-SjGNChywlFkXUPQKHk0b3DLvp7uJ2dN0xQNFhevi94Do2YcI25nRifsesuXHKl4IoCk6FRTxnrpj https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5QCVKKTliCBO44kWXxiJKJcXnylU6tU-wx2y5py3c8E22AWyega9JOySQ</value>
