          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Crane Prairie Reservoir</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v42zoURbJ0VDnzGvuOoTFEgCShsDDdeedsKCWIXxBRgCERRMSx_F8XId89O0XgZlY7zkwVaR9sBdboQ6XCH1Psaup66ghGiTiuEwUi9WT_LMixasoe6tUnV7YnMfEBytgHTY11XzEr-qodgYzoPyFfe6vWOaBA4kwlN-yQ" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is a 5-square-mile reservoir located in the heart of one of Oregon's richest wildlife areas. The reservoir ranges from 10-20 feet deep and is a premier fishery for large rainbow trout and brook trout. Largemouth bass and kokanee are also available.<br><br>Hatchery released rainbow trout are all marked with clipped adipose fins. Harvest is limited to five trout per day with only one fish over 20 inches, wild rainbow trout must be released.<br><br>Large numbers of brook trout are available, with the best fishing early and late in the season. Fish for brook trout at dawn and dusk with flies, lures and bait. Anglers after bigger brook trout should cast their fly, lure or bait close to cover such as submerged logs or undercut banks.<br><br>Crane Prairie offers fair to good largemouth bass fishing opportunities, which improve as water temperature increase. These fish typically range from 2-7 pounds.<br><br>There are good boat ramps at Rock Creek, Quinn River Campground (http://www.fs.usda.gov/wps/portal/fsinternet/!ut/p/c4/04_SB8K8xLLM9MSSzPy8xBz9CP0os3gDfxMDT8MwRydLA1cj72BTJw8jAwjQL8h2VAQAzHJMsQ!!?ss=110601&ttype=recarea&recid=38958&actid=29&navtype=BROWSEBYSUBJECT&position=BROWSEBYSUBJECT&navid=110000000000000&pnavid=&cid=null&pname=Central+Oregon+-+Quinn+River+Campground) and Crane Prairie Resort (http://www.crane-prairie-resort-guides.com/). The resort offers lodging, meals and supplies. Motorized boats are allowed but are restricted to 10 m.p.h.<br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout, brook trout, kokanee, largemouth bass, crappie<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/central-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)<br><br><img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v4ETDkrvOhVqKWr9KRqKVW5kD2QPmflGvZONzabTnNgE_4KXPT0Vg" height="200" width="auto" />]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v42zoURbJ0VDnzGvuOoTFEgCShsDDdeedsKCWIXxBRgCERRMSx_F8XId89O0XgZlY7zkwVaR9sBdboQ6XCH1Psaup66ghGiTiuEwUi9WT_LMixasoe6tUnV7YnMfEBytgHTY11XzEr-qodgYzoPyFfe6vWOaBA4kwlN-yQ https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v4ETDkrvOhVqKWr9KRqKVW5kD2QPmflGvZONzabTnNgE_4KXPT0Vg</value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -121.837006,43.782993,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Crescent Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5Z1AkjH2T_ZLwIK43qH47ICnaXVjZZX_erNcqzuZXo5_NXaB-kXnNi1OCTgK3yc2DeZYu4e4hmdmQWaiiSN4vocIqzs_lRFEL0MZjHInvYe64jZYajPmwVjC3ly2GPWUqAMHReTHVsA7O3kbUPWRCRCA" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is a 6-square-mile lake located within the Deschutes National Forest (http://www.fs.usda.gov/centraloregon) about 75 miles south of Eugene, Oregon. Open year-around, this large, deep lake produces lake trout ranging from 5 to 20 pounds.Crescent Lake also has a good kokanee fishery, producing fish in the 12-13" range. The lake is regularly stocked with brown and rainbow trout.<br><br>Camping is available aty Crescent Lake (http://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/centraloregon/recreation/camping-cabins/recarea/?recid=39060&actid=29), Spring (http://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/centraloregon/recreation/camping-cabins/recarea/?recid=39102&actid=29) and Contorta Point (http://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/centraloregon/recreation/camping-cabins/recarea/?recid=39052&actid=29) campgrounds. Picnic facilities are available at Simax Beach, Tandy Bay and Tranquil Cove. Cabins are available for rent at Crescent Lake Resort (http://crescentlakeresort.com/), which also has a restarant, store, and boat rentals.<br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout, brown trout, lake trout, kokanee<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/central-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5Z1AkjH2T_ZLwIK43qH47ICnaXVjZZX_erNcqzuZXo5_NXaB-kXnNi1OCTgK3yc2DeZYu4e4hmdmQWaiiSN4vocIqzs_lRFEL0MZjHInvYe64jZYajPmwVjC3ly2GPWUqAMHReTHVsA7O3kbUPWRCRCA</value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -121.973305,43.501033,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Delintment Reservoir</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v58DGeQlSLuuQT1hsbLUf5kpT6cQI1r-brhhhRInMBT3g0PFcwWbWj42BkLbT_TGCyEidRR6y_4h-R7FDSj_caAZMsw_Z7-ORuQltwwq2TlmNg0AZBBUpM-lc4XTYubmRo_J6LV3L-Zyhq4UPMeuiHYqTjj_Q" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is a 50-acre reservoir located in the Ochoco National Forest (http://www.fs.usda.gov/centraloregon) approximately 47 miles northwest of Burns, Oregon. This lake is situated within a ponderosa pine forest and offers good bank access. Boats are allowed on the reservoir but are restricted to a 5 m.p.h. speed limit. Fishing is best in the spring and early summer, as the reservoir can become choked with aquatic vegetation in the summer.<br> <br>A large campground with overnight camping, day-use area, boat lauch and accessible boat dock is located on-site.<br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southeast-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v58DGeQlSLuuQT1hsbLUf5kpT6cQI1r-brhhhRInMBT3g0PFcwWbWj42BkLbT_TGCyEidRR6y_4h-R7FDSj_caAZMsw_Z7-ORuQltwwq2TlmNg0AZBBUpM-lc4XTYubmRo_J6LV3L-Zyhq4UPMeuiHYqTjj_Q</value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -119.625953,43.890161,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Deadhorse Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v7rGEqNismqKHGdx6tBPqZbburmiq0A-1_zfoW7ydpUhgSyQD40h5x12YPK1hBEUMi4F7_9snXgbMPaTHJQXCNErzGBM0waCH0NBaKPnlaXjHkIDXq2nzx4RepLLmCcp5pZks_eBePL8PkYG7UpQw-N8BHS7w" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is a 31-acrelake located in a high mountain setting on the Fremont-WinemaNational Forest (http://www.fs.usda.gov/fremont-winema) approximately 30 miles southeast of Paisley, Oregon.Located at an elevation of 7,372 ft., this lake is not accessible until late-Junebecause of snow. The lake is stocked annually with legal- and trophy-sizedrainbow trout throughout the summer. Small boats can be launched but arerestricted to electric motors and a 5 m.p.h. speed limit. Camping is availablenearby at Deadhorse Lake Campground (http://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/fremont-winema/recreation/wateractivities/recarea/?recid=59761&actid=78).<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southeast-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1573-0F9D58</styleUrl>
