            -120.777018,42.55689,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Devils Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v7z76Qv-roI0K9UbxpfTi6VkhKcQ_1qJmPK0SumB1t5eBXsDasI2SPfPptukZbFTzaQRzZiQLFxonJVuTlCWovuJeRwFWaQA3U5vC_i3XtTUQQ9QqZHqACWA9RkZ6OSu_3AyvQJbmqpH6T5GD9AM9tQ_coO" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Devils Lake is a beautiful 23-acre shallow lake located adjacent to Century Drive about 30 miles southwest of Bend, Oregon.The exquisite turquoise color of the water coupled with the scenic views makes this lake a delightful place to visit. The easy access, fishable shoreline and stocking of catchable rainbows make Devils Lake an excellent place to take children fishing. In addition to the stocked rainbows there is a natural reproducing population of brook trout.<br><br>Devils Lake is a shallow lake with an average depth of just over three feet and a maximum depth of 10 feet. Motorized boats are prohibited on this body of water.<br><br>Small boats or rafts can be launched near the campground.<br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southeast-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v7z76Qv-roI0K9UbxpfTi6VkhKcQ_1qJmPK0SumB1t5eBXsDasI2SPfPptukZbFTzaQRzZiQLFxonJVuTlCWovuJeRwFWaQA3U5vC_i3XtTUQQ9QqZHqACWA9RkZ6OSu_3AyvQJbmqpH6T5GD9AM9tQ_coO</value>
