      <Placemark>
        <name>Dog Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v7lXnF4RBF8lwBdOFTSZ82353R65apGdFTPD-W5ZvP2Z_JTef05qnn99EaSfSGNythHjszA_Ws-jhO9lsM2TMRe1Oix9v1yiQX1iJN_Ci1p9Ca3dVnUrNQ8qfMP3tBjruBETUc59dJGVIEFY9gd" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is 51- acre reservoir with a 30’ maximum depth. The lake is located on the Fremont-Winema National Forest (http://www.fs.usda.gov/fremont-winema). The lake contains largemouth bass, yellow perch, crappie, bluegill, brown bullhead, chub, and redband trout. Redband trout must be immediately released. The reservoir has two campgrounds, one on the lake and one about ½ mile from the lake. A boat ramp and pit toilets are available.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout<br> <br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southeast-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1573-0F9D58</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v7lXnF4RBF8lwBdOFTSZ82353R65apGdFTPD-W5ZvP2Z_JTef05qnn99EaSfSGNythHjszA_Ws-jhO9lsM2TMRe1Oix9v1yiQX1iJN_Ci1p9Ca3dVnUrNQ8qfMP3tBjruBETUc59dJGVIEFY9gd</value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
