          <coordinates>
            -118.914771,44.013126,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Pole Creek Reservoir</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v6i20szKjHucBFBlGzsXm4ki2Basr-c0TlowprudE2O_xVvSrznvB4Ii-4cME854gm7_tcgqYJgYpqEr_ufcJoAKC8mFHvrKiMVREeKKmNrKyNjJH6Fj4FQKegfXRgEQp-3G1FrJiGMOrUEpMidk90wGnuo-3kqAjui" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is a 200-acre irrigation reservoir located 25 miles north of Vale, Oregon via US Hwy 26. The reservoir sometimes dries up but is stocked in the spring with both fingerling-sized and catchable rainbow trout. The reservoir is located on private land so it is day-use only with no overnight camping.<br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southeast-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v6i20szKjHucBFBlGzsXm4ki2Basr-c0TlowprudE2O_xVvSrznvB4Ii-4cME854gm7_tcgqYJgYpqEr_ufcJoAKC8mFHvrKiMVREeKKmNrKyNjJH6Fj4FQKegfXRgEQp-3G1FrJiGMOrUEpMidk90wGnuo-3kqAjui</value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -117.55325,44.250671,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Priday Reservoir</name>
        <description><![CDATA[This 210-acre irrigationreservoir is located 5 miles south of Plush, Oregon in the Warner Basin on thewest side of the Plush-Adel road. The reservoir is turbid (muddy) most of thetime and most fish are caught close to shore. Brown bullhead catfish and a fewcrappie are available also. <br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout, brown bullhead catfish, crappie<br> <br><br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southeast-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1573-0F9D58</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -119.902425,42.340465,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Prineville Reservoir</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v4Vy9li7_JrWZfF4jVJLqAHN33xC08VZL1mmojNsUGsbZsE4ZZjzNibyz5W1SU71QSpcfoA8PUhcypsbydAxhVD-7ZJWN-nAYuwpufQkW_clINwNr6Ep50VieH6Yh46Cz5reHKRw8RDSRKLDAVjTwffHM7VVu9cKrdR" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is a 3,000-acre reservoir located approximately 17 miles southeast of Prineville. This reservoir was created for irrigation and flood control by damming the Crooked River behind Arthur R. Bowman Dam. It is situated at an elevation of 3,200 ft. and reaches depths of up to 120 ft.<br><br>The reservoir is open to motorized boats and supports a diverse population of fish, including rainbow trout, black crappie and smallmouth and largemouth bass. The reservoir is stocked annually with sublegal rainbow trout. A boat ramp, boot moorage, picnic areas are available at Prineville Reservoir State Park (http://www.oregonstateparks.org/park_34.php). Lodging and supplies are available at the Prineville Reservoir Resort.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, smallmouth bass, largemouth bass, black crappie, brown bullhead<br> <br>ODFW Recreation Report (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/RR/central/)<br><br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/central-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v4Vy9li7_JrWZfF4jVJLqAHN33xC08VZL1mmojNsUGsbZsE4ZZjzNibyz5W1SU71QSpcfoA8PUhcypsbydAxhVD-7ZJWN-nAYuwpufQkW_clINwNr6Ep50VieH6Yh46Cz5reHKRw8RDSRKLDAVjTwffHM7VVu9cKrdR</value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
        <Point>
