      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Three Creeks Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v6v7JAFKQ2wSmgY32HHwkrq4z7syS9-clseAsFZvcrm2a_LozhQefjrqPSgJcJktnmQcua6GmMP53DJH6wqd8vX6ot8ShB0hEwAzbajzdB-prHeydyd6zZr195NXCQH66nVhZxRVsbuRWa7qlSwyZxLMbFtubI" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is a 28-acre lake in the Deschutes National Forest. It is approximately 20 miles south of Sisters. Situated at an elevation of 6,500 feet in a beautiful cirque below Tam McCarthur Rim, this lake is often snowbound until May or June. Camping is available on the north shore of the lake at Driftwood Campground. Angling is excellent via trolling from a boat or canoe. Fly angling with float tubes is also popular.<br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout, brook trout<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/central-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
